apida y profunda)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"84","parent":"80","text":"Aliento cetonico (olor a frutas/acetona)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"85","parent":"80","text":"Deshidratacion (mucosas secas, turgencia disminuida, taquicardia)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"86","parent":"80","text":"Compromiso de conciencia variable segun severidad","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"87","parent":"79","text":"Laboratorio","guid":"","children":[{"id":"88","parent":"87","text":"Glicemia >250 mg/dL (adultos) o >200 (pediatria)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"89","parent":"88","text":"EXCEPCION: CAD eucglicemica por iSGLT2","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"90","parent":"87","text":"Gases arteriales o venosos → pH <7,3","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"91","parent":"87","text":"Bicarbonato <18 mEq/L","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"92","parent":"87","text":"Beta-hidroxibutirato >=3 mmol/L (GOLD STANDARD, ADA 2024)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"93","parent":"92","text":"Preferir sobre cetonuria → mas rapido y preciso","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"94","parent":"87","text":"Anion gap elevado (>12)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"95","parent":"94","text":"Anion gap = Na - (Cl + HCO3)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"96","parent":"87","text":"Cetonuria positiva (++ o +++)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"97","parent":"79","text":"Examenes\\Ncomplementarios","guid":"YGZdhFpVGmDviW11xwSTKw","children":[{"id":"98","parent":"97","text":"ELP (Na, K,\\NCl, Mg, PO4)","guid":"GhUy2BXAnP3oh-YTD3zYUA","children":[{"id":"99","parent":"98","text":"Na corregido = Na medido + 1,6 por cada 100 mg/dL glicemia >100","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"100","parent":"98","text":"K serico PUEDE ESTAR NORMAL O ALTO pese a deficit corporal total","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"101","parent":"97","text":"Funcion renal (BUN, creatinina)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"102","parent":"97","text":"Hemograma (leucocitosis por estres → no implica infeccion)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"103","pa