na → shift K+ del VIC al VEC","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"141","parent":"138","text":"Al corregir acidosis e iniciar insulina → K+ BAJA RAPIDAMENTE","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"142","parent":"137","text":"NUNCA administrar K a velocidad >0,5 mEq/kg/h","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"143","parent":"136","text":"Protocolo","guid":"","children":[{"id":"144","parent":"143","text":"K >5,5 mEq/L → NO aportar, controlar cada 1-2h","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"145","parent":"143","text":"K 3,5-5,5 mEq/L → KCl 20-40 mEq/L en solucion IV","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"146","parent":"143","text":"K <3,5 mEq/L → KCl 40 mEq/L IV + DIFERIR INSULINA hasta K >3,5","guid":"","children":[{"id":"147","parent":"146","text":"ALERTA: iniciar insulina con K <3,5 puede causar arritmia letal","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"148","parent":"136","text":"Control cada 1-2 horas","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"149","parent":"136","text":"Meta: mantener K entre 4,0-5,0 mEq/L","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"150","parent":"109","text":"Insulina","guid":"","children":[{"id":"151","parent":"150","text":"Conceptos\\Nclave","guid":"opZRL0ljKKL7-rAo-w0pnA","children":[{"id":"152","parent":"151","text":"NO iniciar insulina antes de confirmar K >3,5 mEq/L","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"153","parent":"151","text":"Insulina en BIC se mantiene 2h despues de administrar dosis SC","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"154","parent":"150","text":"Protocolo\\NADULTOS","guid":"Lk_kkCbmQcwfPYLNoKwJ8A","children":[{"id":"155","parent":"154","text":"Insulina cristalina IV en BIC 0,1 U/kg/h (sin bolo, ADA 2024)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"156","parent":"155","text":"ALTERNATIVA: bolo 0,1 U/kg IV + BIC 0,1 U/kg/h","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"157","parent":"154","text":"Objetivo: descenso glicemia 50-75 mg/dL/h","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"158","parent":"154","text":"Si descenso >75-100 mg/dL/h → reducir a 0,05 U/kg/h","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"159","parent":"154","text":"Si des