","parent":"176","text":"Hipokalemia","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"179","parent":"176","text":"Edema cerebral (pediatria)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"180","parent":"176","text":"Alcalosis de rebote","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"181","parent":"109","text":"Fosfato","guid":"","children":[{"id":"182","parent":"181","text":"Reposicion si PO4 <1,0 mg/dL","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"183","parent":"181","text":"20-30 mEq fosfato potasico en reemplazo parcial de KCl","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"184","parent":"181","text":"Previene debilidad muscular respiratoria y rabdomiolisis","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"185","parent":"0","text":"Criterios de Resolucion\\N(ADA/EASD 2024)","guid":"H3hRpaLy5n8bDtjTxET1Lg","children":[{"id":"186","parent":"185","text":"Cumplir AL\\NMENOS 2 de 3","guid":"BIwws6thXHj8RPZYB0lNUQ","children":[{"id":"187","parent":"186","text":"Beta-hidroxibutirato <0,6 mmol/L","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"188","parent":"186","text":"pH venoso >=7,3","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"189","parent":"186","text":"HCO3 >=18 mEq/L","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"190","parent":"185","text":"Y ADEMAS","guid":"","children":[{"id":"191","parent":"190","text":"Anion gap <=12 o normalizado","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"192","parent":"190","text":"Paciente alerta y tolerando via oral","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"193","parent":"0","text":"Complicaciones\\Ndel Tratamiento","guid":"xyRc-Pc-vkqyk__fo4DwFg","children":[{"id":"194","parent":"193","text":"Edema cerebral →\\NMAS TEMIDA en\\Npediatria","guid":"DxnaHWcvL502Ku97mcoc9A","children":[{"id":"195","parent":"194","text":"Incidencia 0,3-1% de CAD pediatricas","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"196","parent":"194","text":"Mortalidad 20-25%","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"197","parent":"194","text":"Factores de riesgo","guid":"","children":[{"id":"198","parent":"197","text":"Correccion rapida de osmolaridad","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"199","parent":"197","text":"Exceso de fluidos en primeras horas","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"200","parent":"197","text":"Uso de bicarbonato","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"201","parent":"197","text":"Menores de 5 anios","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"202","parent":"194","text":"Clinica: cefalea, deterioro conciencia, bradicardia, hipertension","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"203","parent":"194","text":"Manejo: manitol 0,5-1 g/kg IV o SSH 3% 5 mL/kg","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"204","parent":"193","text":"Hipokalemia →\\NRIESGO VITAL","guid":"AOyR-IojRuIGJOwB-SgEow","children":[{"id":"205","parent":"204","text":"Por shift al VIC al corregir acidosis + efecto insulina","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"206","parent":"204","text":"Monitorear K cada 1-2h SIEMPRE","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"207","parent":"193","text":"Hipoglicemia","guid":"","children":[{"id":"208","parent":"207","text":"Por insulinoterapia excesiva","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"209","parent":"207","text":"Iniciar SG 5-10% cuando glicemia <200 mg/dL","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"210","parent":"193","text":"Sobrehidratacion","guid":"","children":[{"id":"211","parent":"210","text":"Riesgo en pediatria, adultos mayores, ICC, ERC","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"212","parent":"210","text":"Aportes orales de padres (pediatria) → considerar en balance","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"213","parent":"193","text":"Hipofosfatemia","guid":"","children":[{"id":"214","parent":"213","text":"Debilidad muscular, insuficiencia respiratoria","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"215","parent":"193","text":"Acidosis hipercloremica","guid":"","children":[{"id":"216","parent":"215","text":"Por exceso de SF 0,9% → considerar soluciones balanceadas","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"217","parent":"193","text":"Tromboembolismo venoso","guid":"","children":[{"id":"218","parent":"217","text":"Riesgo aumentado en CAD → profilaxis con HBPM en adultos","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"219","parent":"0","text":"CAD Eucglicemica\\Npor iSGLT2","guid":"c_CW9KQeiCmCOgi0slx4pw","children":[{"id":"220","parent":"219","text":"Glicemia puede ser <250 mg/dL","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"221","parent":"219","text":"iSGLT2: empagliflozina, dapagliflozina, canagliflozina","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"222","parent":"219","text":"Mecanismo → glucosuria persistente reduce glicemia pero no cetogenesis","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"223","parent":"219","text":"Sospecha: paciente con iSGLT2 + nauseas + acidosis metabolica + anion gap elevado","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"224","parent":"219","text":"Manejo → similar pero REQUIERE aporte de glucosa desde el inicio","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"225","parent":"219","text":"Suspender iSGLT2 al menos 3 dias antes de cirugia electiva","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"226","parent":"0","text":"Consideraciones\\Nen Adulto Mayor","guid":"Dx0Fjq_53_iDe_knglIS1w","children":[{"id":"227","parent":"226","text":"Mayor mortalidad (5-16%) vs jovenes","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"228","parent":"226","text":"Presentacion atipica → delirium, caidas, inapetencia","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"229","parent":"226","text":"Comorbilidades: ICC, ERC → ajustar velocidad de hidratacion","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"230","parent":"226","text":"Riesgo de sobrehidratacion → usar 250 mL/h maximo, monitorizar ingurgitacion yugular","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"231","parent":"226","text":"Polifarmacia → revisar interacciones, suspender metformina y iSGLT2","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"232","parent":"226","text":"Hipokalemia mas peligrosa → mayor riesgo arritmia (cardiopatia previa)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"233","parent":"226","text":"Fragilidad → considerar objetivos de tratamiento y proporcionalidad terapeutica","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"234","parent":"226","text":"Delirium como complicacion frecuente → CAM, medidas no farmacologicas","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"235","parent":"226","text":"Valorar estado funcional previo para definir intensidad terapeutica","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"236","parent":"0","text":"Perlas Clinicas","guid":"","children":[{"id":"237","parent":"236","text":"Beta-hidroxibutirato serico > cetonuria para diagnostico y seguimiento (ADA 2024)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"238","parent":"236","text":"K <3,5 → DIFERIR insulina hasta corregir, riesgo arritmia letal","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"239","parent":"236","text":"CAD eucglicemica por iSGLT2 → sospechar si acidosis + anion gap con glicemia normal","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"240","parent":"236","text":"Leucocitosis en CAD es por estres, NO implica infeccion → buscar foco de todas formas","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"241","parent":"236","text":"Soluciones balanceadas (RL, Plasma-Lyte) resuelven CAD mas rapido que SF (MA 2024)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"242","parent":"236","text":"En adulto mayor: hidratar con cautela (max 250 mL/h), vigilar sobrecarga","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"243","parent":"236","text":"NO usar bicarbonato a menos que pH <6,9 → riesgo edema cerebral y alcalosis rebote","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"244","parent":"236","text":"La hidratacion SOLA reduce glicemia hasta 80 mg/dL/h antes de insulina","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"245","parent":"236","text":"Dolor abdominal en CAD puede simular abdomen agudo → resuelve con tratamiento","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"246","parent":"236","text":"Transicion a insulina SC: iniciar 1-2h ANTES de suspender BIC IV","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"247","parent":"0","text":"VER TAMBIEN","guid":"","children":[{"id":"248","parent":"247","text":"→ Insulinoterapia (Farmacologia)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"249","parent":"247","text":"→ Emergencias Hiperglicemicas HHS (Endocrinologia)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"250","parent":"247","text":"→ Delirium (Geriatria)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"251","parent":"247","text":"→ Equilibrio Acido-Base (Fisiologia)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"252","parent":"247","text":"→ Manejo de Fluidos IV (Cuidados Criticos)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"253","parent":"0","text":"Referencias","guid":"","children":[{"id":"254","parent":"253","text":"1. Umpierrez GE et al. Hyperglycaemic crises in adults with diabetes: a consensus report. Diabetologia. 2024;67(8):1455-79. DOI: 10.1007/s00125-024-06183-8","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"255","parent":"253","text":"2. Dhatariya KK. Management of DKA in adults: updated guideline from JBDS. Diabet Med. 2022;39(6):e14788. DOI: 10.1111/dme.14788","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"256","parent":"253","text":"3. Szabo GV et al. Balanced electrolyte solutions vs 0.9% saline in DKA: systematic review and meta-analysis. Diabetes Metab Res Rev. 2024;40(5):e3831. DOI: 10.1002/dmrr.3831","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"257","parent":"253","text":"4. Rodriguez Alvarez P et al. Hyperglycemic crises in adults: 2024 consensus report review. Cleve Clin J Med. 2025;92(3):152-8. DOI: 10.3949/ccjm.92a.24089","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"258","parent":"253","text":"5. Wolfsdorf JI et al. ISPAD Clinical Practice Consensus Guidelines 2018: DKA and HHS. Pediatr Diabetes. 2018;19(Suppl 27):155-77.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"259","parent":"253","text":"6. Kitabchi AE et al. Hyperglycemic crises in adult patients with diabetes. Diabetes Care. 2009;32(7):1335-43.","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},"node_count":259,"relations":[],"cross_references":[],"specialty":"UCI/Medicina Crítica","folder":"Entidades clínicas/UCI-Medicina Crítica","filename":"CAD Cetoacidosis Diabetica iPad","id":"map_2302","resolved_references":[],"title_raw":"CAD Cetoacidosis Diabetica iPad"}